original: Lundgren, Gustaf Adolf, tandläkare, Ronneby, f. 17/7/09 i Vindeln, Väs-terb. 1., av kyrkoh. Per L. o. Augusta Kärrman. G. 34 m. Ingeborg Gieseke. Barn: Karin f. 35, Per-Olof 37, Brita 45. — Stud:ex. i Umeå 27, tandl:-kand. 29, tandläkare 31. Assist, i Västerås 31, praktik i Ronneby o. Kallinge sed. 32. Kassör i Blek. tandl:-fören. 33-38. Hobbies: fiske, filateli.
translated: Lundgren, Gustaf Adolf, dentist, Ronneby, born on July 17, 1909 in Vindeln, Västerbotten. Son of church minister Per L. and Augusta Kärrman. Married in 1934 to Ingeborg Gieseke. Children: Karin, born in 1935; Per-Olof, born in 1937; Brita, born in 1945. Completed high school in Umeå in 1927, dental studies in 1929, became a dentist in 1931. Assistant in Västerås in 1931, practiced in Ronneby and Kallinge since 1932. Treasurer at the Blekinge Dental Association from 1933 to 1938. Hobbies include fishing and philately.
